    {
      "id": "c4817b66_6d5b59c7",
      "patchset_number": 16,
      "message": "Yes. Although they are actually different certs in the ZIP:\n- Basically there is 2-way TLS here, where both server and client need to authenticate, so they each need to have certs signed by the CA (certificate authority).\n- PNF Sim is the RestConf server, which has a server cert and key, as well as a CA cert to validate incoming client requests.\n- SDNC is the RestConf client, which has a different cert and key, signed by CA.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
      "updated": "2024-07-24 16:29:32.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "6b1da97f_7aae9916",
      "unresolved": false
